# v1 → v2 Migration Strategy

## Overview

Gradual migration using feature flags to minimize risk.

## Approach

### Phase 1: Feature Flag Setup
```typescript
// Feature flag provider
const V2_ENABLED_KEY = 'enable-v2-portal';

function useV2Enabled() {
  const [enabled, setEnabled] = useLocalStorage(V2_ENABLED_KEY, false);
  return { enabled, toggle: () => setEnabled(!enabled) };
}

// Router logic
function App() {
  const { enabled } = useV2Enabled();

  if (enabled) {
    return <V2App />;
  }
  return <V1App />;
}
```

### Phase 2: Opt-in Beta (Week 1-2)
- Internal team only
- Add toggle in user menu: "Try New Portal"
- Collect feedback
- Fix critical bugs

### Phase 3: Gradual Rollout (Week 3-6)
- 10% of users (random selection)
- Monitor error rates, performance
- Increase to 25%, 50%, 75%
- Full 100% when stable

### Phase 4: Cleanup (Week 7+)
- Remove v1 code
- Move `/src/v2` to `/src`
- Update all imports
- Remove feature flags

## Risk Mitigation

### Monitoring
- Error tracking (Sentry)
- Performance metrics (Web Vitals)
- User feedback form
- Rollback trigger: >5% error rate increase

### Rollback Plan
```typescript
// Emergency rollback
localStorage.setItem('force-v1', 'true');
window.location.reload();
```

### Communication
- Release notes
- Migration guide for users
- Support documentation
- Feedback channels
